Uttar Pradesh
Nov 04, 2014
Abduction, Murder
Description:
			Four persons have been sentenced to life imprisonment by a local court here for abducting and murdering a 12-year-old boy.

Additional District and Sessions Judge Harish Tripathi also imposed a fine of Rs 20,000 each on the four - Imran, Farman, Gaffar and Budhu yesterday after holding them guilty of murder.

The victim Talib was abducted for ransom. Later his body was recovered from Bhesani village in Shamli district on January 13, 2011.


